<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1792,2008]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,283,1792,1818]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male: Eyes approximate but not contiguous above antennae; vt absent; femora mainly brown, except apically; pulvilli I and II as long as t 
<number box="[691,699,1846,1860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="5.0">5</number>
, claws present; abdominal sternites with long vestiture, St 
<number box="[1423,1436,1830,1856]" pageId="5" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
without striking bristles. Dorsal surface of surstylus with a crease; arms of postgonite with few microtrichia proximally; male cercus subtriangular.
</paragraph>
